E.129.100 - The system shall support the ability to enable/disable Configuration Monitor external module.
E.129.200 - The system shall support the ability to enable Configuration Monitor external module on all projects by default.
E.129.300 - The system shall support the ability to make Configuration Monitor external module discoverable by users.
E.129.400 - The system shall support the ability to allow non-admins to enable Configuration Monitor external module on projects.
E.129.500 - The system shall support the ability to hide Configuration Monitor external module from non-admins in the list of enabled modules on each project.
E.129.600 - The system shall support the ability to configure 'Module configuration permissions in projects' for Configuration Monitor external module.
E.129.700 - The system shall support the ability to view the usage of Configuration Monitor external module.
E.129.800 - The system shall allow enabling or disabling System Changes tracking at the system level.
E.129.900 - The system shall allow enabling or disabling Project Changes tracking at the project level.
E.129.1000 - The system shall allow enabling or disabling User Role Changes tracking at the project level.
E.129.1100 - The system shall register a cron job (configuration_monitor_cron) when the module is enabled at the system level.
E.129.1200 - The system shall retain system-level and project-level changes when the module is disabled to maintain historical audit data.
E.129.1300 - The system shall require at least one tracking option—Project Changes or User Role Changes—to be enabled at the project level.
E.129.1400 - The system shall allow configuring the maximum number of days to display on change log pages at both the system and project levels.
E.129.1500 - The system shall allow configuring the maximum number of hours for email notifications at both the system and project levels.
E.129.1600 - The system shall allow enabling or disabling email notifications at both the system and project levels.
E.129.1700 - The system shall allow configuring email settings (from and to address) at both the system and project levels.
E.129.1800 - The system shall validate that email settings are complete when email notifications are enabled at either the system or project level.
E.129.1900 - The system shall restrict Configuration Monitor settings to super users only at both the system and project levels.
E.129.2000 - The system shall display the changes in a tabular format for both System Changes, Project Changes and User Role changes.
E.129.2100 - The system shall support the ability to filter displayed values for System Changes, Project Changes, and User Role Changes.
E.129.2200 - The system shall display instrument-specific privilege changes for Data Export and Data Entry in User Role Changes.
E.129.2300 - The system shall restrict access to the System Changes page to super users only.
E.129.2400 - The system shall restrict access to Project Changes and User Role Changes pages to users with user_rights privilege or super user status.
E.129.2500 - The system shall display the System Changes link in the Control Center's External Modules section when System Changes is enabled.
E.129.2600 - The system shall display the Project Changes link when Project Changes is enabled.
E.129.2700 - The system shall display the User Role Changes link when User Role Changes is enabled.
E.129.2800 - The system shall send automated email summaries containing System Changes when changes occur and email notifications are enabled.
E.129.2900 - The system shall send automated email summaries containing Project Changes and/or User Role Changes when changes occur and email notifications are enabled at the project level.
E.129.3000 - The system shall support the ability to export configuration changes to CSV format for System Changes, Project Changes, and User Role Changes.